# Build Seeknal Analytics Layer

Create semantic models, metrics, and exposures for analytics and reporting.

## When to Use

Use this skill when asked to create business metrics, dashboards, reports, semantic layers, or KPI definitions.

## Workflow

### 1. Semantic Model (Dimensions + Measures)

```bash
seeknal draft semantic_model <name>
```

```yaml
kind: semantic_model
name: sales_model
inputs:
  - ref: transform.daily_sales
dimensions:
  - name: region
    type: categorical
    column: region
    description: "Sales region"
  - name: sale_date
    type: time
    column: sale_date
    description: "Date of sale"
measures:
  - name: total_revenue
    type: sum
    column: revenue
    description: "Sum of revenue"
  - name: order_count
    type: count
    column: order_id
    description: "Number of orders"
  - name: avg_order_value
    type: average
    column: revenue
    description: "Average order value"
```

### 2. Metrics (KPIs, Ratios, Cumulative)

```bash
seeknal draft metric <name>
```

**Simple metric:**
```yaml
kind: metric
name: monthly_revenue
type: simple
inputs:
  - ref: semantic_model.sales_model
measure: total_revenue
time_dimension: sale_date
time_grains: [day, week, month]
filters:
  - "region IS NOT NULL"
```

**Derived metric (ratio):**
```yaml
kind: metric
name: revenue_per_order
type: derived
inputs:
  - ref: metric.monthly_revenue
  - ref: metric.order_count
expression: "monthly_revenue / NULLIF(order_count, 0)"
```

**Cumulative metric:**
```yaml
kind: metric
name: cumulative_revenue
type: cumulative
inputs:
  - ref: semantic_model.sales_model
measure: total_revenue
time_dimension: sale_date
window: 90d
```

### 3. Exposures (Reports + Dashboards)

```bash
seeknal draft exposure <name>
```

```yaml
kind: exposure
name: sales_dashboard
type: dashboard
owner:
  name: Analytics Team
  email: analytics@company.com
description: "Weekly sales performance dashboard"
depends_on:
  - ref: metric.monthly_revenue
  - ref: metric.revenue_per_order
  - ref: transform.daily_sales
url: "https://dashboards.company.com/sales"
maturity: production
```

### 4. Validate & Apply

```bash
seeknal dry-run draft_semantic_model_<name>.yml
seeknal apply draft_semantic_model_<name>.yml

seeknal dry-run draft_metric_<name>.yml
seeknal apply draft_metric_<name>.yml

seeknal dry-run draft_exposure_<name>.yml
seeknal apply draft_exposure_<name>.yml

seeknal plan    # Verify analytics layer in DAG
seeknal run
```

## Dependency Order

Build analytics nodes in this order:
1. **Sources/Transforms** — raw and cleaned data
2. **Semantic Models** — dimensions and measures on top of transforms
3. **Metrics** — KPIs computed from semantic model measures
4. **Exposures** — dashboards and reports consuming metrics

## Common Mistakes

- **Metric without semantic model**: Simple metrics need a `semantic_model.*` input with the referenced measure
- **Circular metric refs**: Derived metrics cannot reference themselves
- **Missing time dimension**: Cumulative and time-grain metrics require `time_dimension`
- **Exposure without depends_on**: Always list what the exposure consumes for lineage tracking
